<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1847,2016]" box="[151,1436,1847,1872]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,333,1847,1871]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male 
<quantity box="[404,504,1847,1871]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="3.8">3.80 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[574,674,1847,1871]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.12" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="1.12">1.12 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes; female 
<quantity box="[965,1065,1847,1871]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.95" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="3.95">3.95 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1135,1235,1847,1871]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.20 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1847,2016]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,498,1882,1907]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Head and thorax (color).</emphasis>
Ground color dark brown with lemon yellow areas on head. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[1287,1370,1883,1907]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 22" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[192,1408,241,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[160,1427,193,1813]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 22. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. Body, lateral and dorsal view: (15 – 16) Igerna delta sp. nov.; (17 – 18) I. neosa (Webb); (19 – 20) I. malagasica sp. nov., male; (21 – 22) same, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283355/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1341,1370,1883,1907]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
) with pair of lemon yellow maculae adjacent to each compound eye contiguous to facial and pronotal ones. Face (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 33" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[215,1378,239,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[192,1396,193,1831]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 33. Species of Agalliini. Face: (23) Agallidwipa biramosa sp. nov.; (24) A. bispinosa sp. nov., male; (25) same, female; (26) A. pauliana (Evans); (27) A. webbi sp. nov., male; (28) same, female; (29) Igerna delta sp. nov.; (30) I. malagasica sp. nov., male; (31) same, female; (32) I. neosa (Webb); (33) Agalliana ensigera Oman." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283356/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,1955,1979]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
) with large lemon yellow marking extending from one eye to the other. Frontoclypeus with median lemon yellow band; lora excepting margins, and genae lemon yellow. Antennae, pedicel and flagellum lemon yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,1223]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[281,413,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 22" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[192,1408,241,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[160,1427,193,1813]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 22. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. Body, lateral and dorsal view: (15 – 16) Igerna delta sp. nov.; (17 – 18) I. neosa (Webb); (19 – 20) I. malagasica sp. nov., male; (21 – 22) same, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283355/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs 
<number box="[342,413,151,175]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="15.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="15.0">15–16</number>
</figureCitation>
) with lateral marginal area and narrow posterior margin lemon yellow. Mesoscutellum lateral margins ochraceous. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[623,758,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 22" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[192,1408,241,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[160,1427,193,1813]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 22. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. Body, lateral and dorsal view: (15 – 16) Igerna delta sp. nov.; (17 – 18) I. neosa (Webb); (19 – 20) I. malagasica sp. nov., male; (21 – 22) same, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283355/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs 
<number box="[687,758,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="15.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="15.0">15–16</number>
</figureCitation>
) dark brown at proximal area becoming paler gradually towards apex, band along costal area except in basal 
<number box="[748,797,223,247]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="0.25">0.25</number>
hyaline, margins ochraceous. Thoracic pleura with paler margins. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[331,416,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 22" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[192,1408,241,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[160,1427,193,1813]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 22. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. Body, lateral and dorsal view: (15 – 16) Igerna delta sp. nov.; (17 – 18) I. neosa (Webb); (19 – 20) I. malagasica sp. nov., male; (21 – 22) same, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283355/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[387,416,260,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
) lemon yellow, protibiae and some areas of other parts specially tarsomeres and claws, fuscous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,1223]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,354,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Morphology.</emphasis>
Face rather polished, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[788,871,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 22" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[192,1408,241,1769]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[160,1427,193,1813]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 22. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. Body, lateral and dorsal view: (15 – 16) Igerna delta sp. nov.; (17 – 18) I. neosa (Webb); (19 – 20) I. malagasica sp. nov., male; (21 – 22) same, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283355/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[843,871,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
) convex, pronotum finely granulose, transversely wrinkled with one depressed transverse area on either side of median line in anterior half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,1223]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,380,403,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[495,581,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 41" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,225,1525]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,193,1562]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 41. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. Genital capsules, lateral view: (34) Igerna delta sp. nov.; (35) I. neosa (Webb); (36) I. malagasica sp. nov.; (37) I. flavocosta sp. nov.; (38) Agallidwipa biramosa sp. nov.; (39) A. webbi sp. nov.; (40) A. bispinosa sp. nov.; (41) A. pauliana (Evans), Arrows point out posterior margin of pygofer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283357/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[550,581,404,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with posterior margin narrowing towards blunt apex, and directed inward; caudodorsal region with serrated process (
<figureCitation box="[832,918,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 70 – 85" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[239,1366,222,1797]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[207,1380,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 70 – 85. Morphological aspects of Agallidwipa and Igerna species. (70 – 73) A. biramosa sp. nov.: (70) profemur; (71) apodemes of second abdominal sternite; (72) connective; (73) X segment processes, lateral view; (74 – 76) A. bispinosa sp. nov.: (74) forewing, lateral view; (75) connective; (76) X segment processes, lateral view; (77 – 79) A. pauliana (Evans): (77) apodemes of second abdominal sternite; (78) pygofer posterior margin; (79) X segment processes, lateral view; (80) A. webbi sp. nov., style and connective, dorsal view; (81 – 82) I. delta sp. nov.: (81) pygofer process, caudal view; (82) connective; (83) I. neosa (Webb), apex of pygofer process; (84 – 85) I. malagasica sp. nov.: (84) pygofer processes, caudal view; (85) connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283361/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[887,918,439,463]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="81.0">81</number>
</figureCitation>
). Valve (
<figureCitation box="[1023,1109,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1569,1592]" captionTargetBox="[168,1420,205,1523]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1548]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 53. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. 42 – 49. Styles, dorsal views (except 46), respectively: (42) Igerna malagasica sp. nov.; (43) I. flavocosta sp. nov.; (44) I. delta sp. nov.; (45) I. neosa (Webb); (46 – 47) Agallidwipa bispinosa sp. nov., lateral and dorsal view respectively; (48) A. biramosa sp. nov.; (49) A. pauliana (Evans). 50 – 53. Subgenital plates, ventral view: (50) I. flavocosta sp. nov.; (51) A. biramosa sp. nov.; (52) I. delta sp. nov.; (53) A. bispinosa sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283358/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1078,1109,439,463]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="52.0">52</number>
</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, as long as subgenital plates. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[561,645,476,500]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1569,1592]" captionTargetBox="[168,1420,205,1523]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1548]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 53. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. 42 – 49. Styles, dorsal views (except 46), respectively: (42) Igerna malagasica sp. nov.; (43) I. flavocosta sp. nov.; (44) I. delta sp. nov.; (45) I. neosa (Webb); (46 – 47) Agallidwipa bispinosa sp. nov., lateral and dorsal view respectively; (48) A. biramosa sp. nov.; (49) A. pauliana (Evans). 50 – 53. Subgenital plates, ventral view: (50) I. flavocosta sp. nov.; (51) A. biramosa sp. nov.; (52) I. delta sp. nov.; (53) A. bispinosa sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283358/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[614,645,476,500]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="52.0">52</number>
</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, fused to valve and to each other along basal portion, narrowed on distal 
<number box="[371,423,511,535]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="0.66">0.66</number>
; apex subacute; in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[792,876,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 41" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,225,1525]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,193,1562]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 41. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. Genital capsules, lateral view: (34) Igerna delta sp. nov.; (35) I. neosa (Webb); (36) I. malagasica sp. nov.; (37) I. flavocosta sp. nov.; (38) Agallidwipa biramosa sp. nov.; (39) A. webbi sp. nov.; (40) A. bispinosa sp. nov.; (41) A. pauliana (Evans), Arrows point out posterior margin of pygofer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283357/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[845,876,511,535]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
), extending posteriorly well beyond pygofer, and lacking hair-like and prominent setae. Styles (
<figureCitation box="[685,773,548,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 53" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1569,1592]" captionTargetBox="[168,1420,205,1523]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1548]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 53. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. 42 – 49. Styles, dorsal views (except 46), respectively: (42) Igerna malagasica sp. nov.; (43) I. flavocosta sp. nov.; (44) I. delta sp. nov.; (45) I. neosa (Webb); (46 – 47) Agallidwipa bispinosa sp. nov., lateral and dorsal view respectively; (48) A. biramosa sp. nov.; (49) A. pauliana (Evans). 50 – 53. Subgenital plates, ventral view: (50) I. flavocosta sp. nov.; (51) A. biramosa sp. nov.; (52) I. delta sp. nov.; (53) A. bispinosa sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283358/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[741,773,548,572]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="44.0">44</number>
</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, well developed, outer fork rounded and short, bearing scattered setae, inner fork longer with basal portion strongly curved and apical portion subacute. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[300,390,620,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 70 – 85" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[239,1366,222,1797]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[207,1380,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 70 – 85. Morphological aspects of Agallidwipa and Igerna species. (70 – 73) A. biramosa sp. nov.: (70) profemur; (71) apodemes of second abdominal sternite; (72) connective; (73) X segment processes, lateral view; (74 – 76) A. bispinosa sp. nov.: (74) forewing, lateral view; (75) connective; (76) X segment processes, lateral view; (77 – 79) A. pauliana (Evans): (77) apodemes of second abdominal sternite; (78) pygofer posterior margin; (79) X segment processes, lateral view; (80) A. webbi sp. nov., style and connective, dorsal view; (81 – 82) I. delta sp. nov.: (81) pygofer process, caudal view; (82) connective; (83) I. neosa (Webb), apex of pygofer process; (84 – 85) I. malagasica sp. nov.: (84) pygofer processes, caudal view; (85) connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283361/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[359,390,620,644]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="82.0">82</number>
</figureCitation>
), well developed and pigmented, narrower anteriorly than posteriorly; posterior margin bearing two lobes directed outwards with same distance between them as their length. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1377,655,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 61" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1440,1463]" captionTargetBox="[157,1416,229,1364]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1419]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 61. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. Aedeagus (except 57), lateral views: (54) Agallidwipa pauliana (Evans); (55) A. bispinosa sp. nov.; (56) A. biramosa sp. nov.; (57) A. webbi sp. nov., style, connective and aedeagus; (58) Igerna delta sp. nov.; (59) I. neosa (Webb); (60) Igerna malagasica sp. nov.; (61) I. flavocosta sp. nov., Arrows point out the ventral projection prominence." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283359/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1392,1423,655,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 69" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1614,1637]" captionTargetBox="[188,1407,217,1575]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[172,1414,193,1593]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 69. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. Aedeagus, ventral views (except 65 &amp; 66): (62) Agallidwipa bispinosa sp. nov.; (63) A. biramosa sp. nov.; (64) A. webbi sp. nov.; (65) A. pauliana (Evans) aedeagus and connective, ventral view;; (66) Igerna delta sp. nov., dorsal view; (67) I. neosa (Webb); (68) I. flavocosta sp. nov.; (69) I. malagasica sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283360/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">66</figureCitation>
), symmetrical; with well developed dorsal apodeme, 
<number box="[754,803,692,716]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="0.66">0.66</number>
times as long as shaft in lateral view; shaft elongate, slightly angularly curved dorsally in middle, again ventrally near apex, with pair of lateral wing-like triangular processes at apical 
<number box="[365,414,764,788]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="0.25">0.25</number>
length, and pair of short apical acute processes directed lateroventrally; gonopore apical on ventral margin. Anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[461,546,799,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 41" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,225,1525]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,193,1562]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 41. Species of Madagascaran Agalliini. Genital capsules, lateral view: (34) Igerna delta sp. nov.; (35) I. neosa (Webb); (36) I. malagasica sp. nov.; (37) I. flavocosta sp. nov.; (38) Agallidwipa biramosa sp. nov.; (39) A. webbi sp. nov.; (40) A. bispinosa sp. nov.; (41) A. pauliana (Evans), Arrows point out posterior margin of pygofer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283357/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[515,546,799,823]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
), with segment X simple, without any process; segment XI with several short spiniform projections on inferior margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,1223]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,384,871,896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Female (color).</emphasis>
Similar to male in coloration except additional hyaline band along claval suture on corium and entire costal area hyaline. Clypellus with median longitudinal stripe dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,1223]" box="[201,937,943,968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
